            "Item1": "[EMAIL - 24##-06-25-13-51-18-1905]\n<>\nSUBJECT: Regulations Approval\nFROM: <corrupt:0xFFFFDC>\nTO: <corrupt:0xFFFF0A>\n<>\nI just got off a holocall with the national regulation board. The food teleportation systems are good to sell! Now we can really push for that single-use packaging ban - and given that our food-boxes already resist spoilage, food waste (and our unprofitable years) will be a thing of the past. And with how lazy people are nowadays, we can certainly adapt this tech to other things.\n<>\nDon't forget to strengthen the thermal shielding of the dropbox. The failure rate is less than 1 in 500, but still... As you know, when E=mc2, and c is so large, that means just the mass of a raisin collapsing into a black hole will immediately (within 10^-25 seconds) evaporate to Hawking radiation, and generate the energy equivalent to the nuclear bomb dropped on Hiroshima. Our systems for reversing the teleportation when this happens are getting better and can take away most of that energy, but we can't let any more leak out.\n<>\nSerendipitously, this solves our abnormally high food usage problem, for now. No one will question why our food delivery department is using food.\n<>\nDo you ever wonder, in an alternate universe, we would have pursued that infinite energy idea?\n\n[END]",
